The article is a transcript of a speech given by Vice President Kamala Harris at the United States Conference of Mayors. She discusses the issue of gun violence and the efforts being made to address it. Harris highlights the progress that has been made through executive orders, federal policies, and the passage of the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act. She also emphasizes the importance of listening to the voices of young people who have been directly affected by gun violence and their calls for action. In addition, Harris touches on the issue of reproductive freedom and the recent Supreme Court decision on abortion rights. She urges respect for women's autonomy and the need to protect their right to make decisions about their own bodies. Harris concludes by emphasizing the importance of elections and the need to elect leaders who will fight for these freedoms.